SUMMARY:Smart City Innovation Showcase
DESCRIPTION:Smart City Innovation Showcase\n​AI • Smart Infrastructure • Smart Buildings • Mobility\n​Cities\, counties\, transit agencies\, utilities\, and ports across the Pacific Northwest are preparing major upcoming infrastructure contracts and modernization initiatives in areas like smart buildings\, mobility systems\, infrastructure monitoring\, and AI-driven operations. \n​This event brings together the people who shape those contracts — and the companies that will help deliver them. We want the right stakeholders in the room before the contracts are released. \n​If you influence public infrastructure projects\, build them\, supply them\, or fund them — this room is for you. \n​Speakers\n​Korean Consul General Eunji Seo \n​Vice President of KOSME \n​Josh Davis – Greater Seattle Partners \n​Brian Surratt – Deputy Mayor of Seattle \n​Who Should Attend\n​Public Sector Leaders : \n​City and County CIOs | Public Works Directors | Transportation & ITS Program Managers Facilities and Clean Buildings Program Leaders | Port\, Transit\, and Utility Operators \n​Infrastructure & Engineering Firms \n​Prime contractors bidding on public projects | Civil and transportation engineering firm | Building modernization and commissioning firms | Infrastructure systems integrators \n​Smart City Investors \n​Aligned Venture Capital | Smart infrastructure and AI technology companies | Infrastructure| and climate-tech investors \n​Why Attend\n​Most public infrastructure contracts are shaped months or years before the RFP is released. This event connects the three groups that determine how those projects come together: \n​ Public-sector program owners responsible for upcoming projects \n​Engineering firms and contractors who typically deliver them \n​Technology innovators developing the next generation of solutions \n​Attendees will gain: \n​Early visibility into upcoming infrastructure programs \n​Contractors and cities can explore how emerging technologies can strengthen \n​Upcoming bids and contract renewals. get to see how tech can shape future bids. \n​Direct access to decision-makers and project owners \n​Opportunities to identify partnerships before contracts are released \n​Insight into how emerging technologies align with real procurement pathways \n​Opportunities to discuss pilot deployments and real infrastructure use cases \n​Even if your current contract does not include Smart City technology\, this forum offers exposure to solutions that can be incorporated into future bids and rebid cycles. \n​What You’ll Experience\n​Smart Infrastructure Technology Showcase: Meet companies building solutions in: \n​Smart buildings\, energy storage\, and energy optimization \n​Transportation infrastructure and intelligent mobility systems \n​Infrastructure monitoring using sensors\, radar\, and drones \n​AI-driven operational analytics \n​Security\, robotics\, and simulation technologies for public facilities \n​Contract Alignment Conversations\n​Explore how emerging technologies align with real infrastructure projects and procurement pathways across the region. \n​Networking with Decision Makers\n​Connect directly with government leaders\, infrastructure contractors\, and investors shaping the future of public infrastructure. \n​Structured introductions are designed to help participants identify partners for upcoming contracts\, pilots\, and future procurements. \n​Accelerate real Smart City deployments across the Pacific Northwest \n​Hosted by\n​Korea SMEs and Startups Agency (KOSME)\nConsulate General of the Republic of Korea in Seattle \n​Organized by K-Startup Seattle\n​In Partnership with Seattle Partners
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/smart-city-innovation-showcase/
